						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">krzysiobal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I have 7.3728MHz, 16MHz, 24MHz, 26MHz, 32MHz and 32.768 kHZ crystals. I can try to use the last one and see under logyc analyzer what addresses the CPU is outputing, but isn't that crystal too slow for that CPU? <br /><br />Also, this CPU cannot execute code step-by-step as far I remember (or can it?)</div>The original 2A03 is NMOS, and it seems to have a minimum φ0 rate of 100kHz; I have no idea what that implies for a famiclone cpu (1.2MHz, maybe?)... but I guess that slow would at least allow you to use your logic analyzer. You could probably build a 1.5MHz source using an asynchronous counter and a 24MHz xtal.<br /><br />Without sufficient underclocking or /RDY I'm not certain how to single-step it.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The 7805 is driven with a 9v DC supply from transformer. [...] draws 180mA @ 5V, which makes the 7805 very hot</div>Well, (9V-5V)* 180mA = 700mW, which will get pretty toasty pretty fast. Even more if the transformer isn't a switcher, probably closer to (13-5V)*180mA = 1.4W</div>

